Yes! Criterion is a great library for microbenchmarks. Here’s a simple example:

```rust
#![feature(test)]
extern crate test;

fn fibonacci(n: u64) -> u64 {
    match n {
        0 | 1 => n,
        _ => fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2),
    }
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod benches {
    extern crate criterion;
    use criterion::{black_box, Criterion};

    pub fn bench_fib(c: &mut Criterion) {
        c.bench_function("fibonacci", |b| b.iter(|| fibonacci(black_box(10))));
    }
}
```
Then you can run the benchmarks with:

```sh
cargo bench
```
Criterion will automatically collect and report statistical significance, making it easy to compare performance across different versions or features.

